
Overview of verb apprise

The verb apprise has 4 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                      
1. advise, notify, give notice, send word, apprise, apprize -- (inform (somebody) of something; "I advised him that the rent was due")
2. instruct, apprise, apprize -- (make aware of; "Have the students been apprised of the tuition hike?")
3. appreciate, apprize, apprise, revalue -- (gain in value; "The yen appreciated again!")
4. appreciate, apprize, apprise -- (increase the value of; "The Germans want to appreciate the Deutsche Mark")
